Installation instructions for FEniCS using the Docker container¶

In this tutorial the step by step instructions for the installation of FEniCS is shown for Ubuntu as well as Windows 10.

This will include the following steps:

  1. Installation of Docker
  2. Download of the FEniCS Docker container
  3. Run the FEniCS container
  4. Start FEniCS

Installation on Ubuntu¶

1. Install Docker¶

Follow the instructions on Docker Homepage. Note: If you have an older Ubuntu version you might run into trouble with user permissions. These problems can be overcome, but require extra effort in the usage of FEniCS. You may rather consider to upgrade to a newer version of Ubuntu and thus Docker.

Test if the installation worked by running

$ docker run hello-world

2. Download FEniCS Docker container¶

$ docker pull quay.io/fenicsproject/stable:latest

3. Run the FEniCS Docker container¶

Copy the following command into your terminal

$ docker run --tty --publish 8888:8888 --workdir=/home/fenics/shared --volume $(pwd):/home/fenics/shared --detach --name fenics-container quay.io/fenicsproject/stable "jupyter-lab --ip=0.0.0.0 --port=8888 --no-browser --allow-root --notebook-dir=$pwd --NotebookApp.token='abcd'"

This will create a Docker container with the name fenics-container and add the current working directory to the container. Also the jupyter-lab is set up with the predefined token abcd.

4. Start the container¶

Type in the following command into your terminal:

$ docker start fenics-container

5. Start Jupyter-Lab¶

Access the following adress via your browser (and save the adress as favourite):

127.0.0.1:8888

or

http://localhost:8888/

in your browser. You need to log in with the token 'abcd'.

6. Proper exit and restart¶

In the JupyterLab you can go to File>Shut Down or alternatively execute

$ docker stop fenics-container
$ docker container ls -a

with the last command you can see the running containers and verify that the fenics container is closed.

In order to start the container again, simply type

$ docker start fenics-container

and start JupyterLab in your browser. Note: You do not need to execute the docker run command.

Installation on Windows¶

1. Install Docker¶

  • Download the Installer 'Docker Desktop for Windows' from Docker Homepage and execute the file.
  • Follow the instructions for WSL 2 backend installation under WSL 2.
  • Open a PowerShell (alternatively press 'Super+R' and type 'cmd' for a command line)
  • Test if the installation worked by typing
docker run hello-world

You should now see a message that confirms the correct installation of Docker.

2. Download FEniCS Docker container¶

Type the following command into a PowerShell or command line:

docker pull quay.io/fenicsproject/stable:latest

3. Create FEniCS Docker container¶

Copy the following command into into a PowerShell

docker run --tty --publish 8888:8888 --workdir=/home/fenics/shared --volume ${PWD}:/home/fenics/shared --detach --name fenics-container quay.io/fenicsproject/stable

You can now open Docker Desktop, which should look like this

4. Start the container and JupyterLab¶

If the stack next to the name 'fenics-container' is grey then you need to start it by clicking the play button. In order to see the play button you have to hover around the 'fenics-container'. Now open a console inside the container by clicking the CLI button, see image below.

A terminal opens up in which you first type

bash

and after you hit enter, type (or copy this code and paste via right click):

jupyter-lab --ip=0.0.0.0 --port=8888 --no-browser --allow-root --notebook-dir=$pwd --NotebookApp.token='abcd'

The Jupyter-Server is now running. Do not close the terminal window. You can open access Jupyter-Lab either by clicking 'open in browser', see image below, or by directly visiting

http://localhost:8888/

in your browser. You may need to log in with the token 'abcd'.

5. Proper exit and restart¶

  • In the JupyterLab you can go to File>Shut Down
  • In the terminal press 'Ctrl+c' and then 'Ctrl+d'
  • In the Docker Desktop application stop the container by clicking the stop button
  • Close Docker Desktop

If you want to restart FEniCS, open the Docker Desktop application and

  • start the container by clicking on the play button for the fenics-container,
  • open a container-terminal via the CLI button
  • type in 'bash' and hit enter
  • use the 'arrow up' key to recover the last command 'jupyter-lab --ip=0.0.0.0 ...' and hit enter again
  • visit again the http://localhost:8888/
